'Propanoic acid' (also known as 'propionic acid' from the Greek words protos =
"first" and pion = "fat) is a naturally occurring carboxylic acid with chemical
formula CH 3CH 2COOH. It is a clear liquid with a pungent
odor. The anion CH 3CH 2COO â as well as the salts
and esters of propanoic acid are known as propanoates (or propionates).
